OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1775135469
OL,3,CCan Trump actually withdraw from Nato?
OL,5,FThe amendment to the National Defense
OL,6,FAuthorisation Act was introduced while
OL,7,FTrump was standing as a presidential
OL,8,Fcandidate for the second time, and his
OL,9,Fmessaging on Nato was still very mixed.
OL,11,FThat ignited debates as to whether the
OL,12,Fpresident did, or should, possess the
OL,13,Fpower to withdraw the US from treaties
OL,14,Fwithout proper approval.
OL,16,FBy that law, even if all the
OL,17,FRepublicans voted with Trump to
OL,18,Fwithdraw from Nato, at least 14
OL,19,FDemocrats would need to agree to it
OL,20,Ffor the legislation to pass.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
