OL,3,CCan Trump actually withdraw from Nato?
OL,5,FThat would be very unlikely to happen,
OL,6,Fespecially as many Republicans are
OL,7,Fstrongly in favour of Nato.
OL,9,FUS Senators Chris Coons (Democrat) and
OL,10,FMitch McConnel (Republican) issued a
OL,11,Fjoint statement on the subject on
OL,12,FWednesday that said: "The United
OL,13,FStates joined NATO in 1949 when the
OL,14,FSenate voted to ratify the NATO
OL,15,Ftreaty, and the United States will
OL,16,Fremain in it. The Senate will continue
OL,17,Fto support the alliance for the peace
OL,18,Fand protection it provides America,
OL,19,FEurope, and the world."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
