OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1775135469
OL,3,CCan Trump actually withdraw from Nato?
OL,5,FAnd it wouldn't be the first time a US
OL,6,Fpresident has withdrawn from a treaty
OL,7,Fwithout explicit approval from
OL,8,FCongress.
OL,10,FIn 2020, Trump left the Open Skies
OL,11,FTreaty, which allowed unarmed
OL,12,Fsurveillance flights over member
OL,13,Fcountries, without congressional
OL,14,Fapproval.
OL,16,FIf Trump tried to do the same with
OL,17,FNato, the matter could end up in
OL,18,Fcourt, according to a report by the
OL,19,FCongressional Research Service.
OL,21,FCould he disrupt Nato from inside?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
